                    <p>This privacy policy of reaprite.com will reflect the method in which Reaprite will collect, use and disclose personal information collected from Users (User) of the Website (Site) or Apps (Android or IOS). The purpose is to inform our Users of our data collection practises in order to protect your privacy.</p>
					
                    <h3 data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="10" style="color: #3C3E82 " class="trim">Information we collect</h3>
                    <p>We collect personal information from a User mostly during the sign up and actual savings processes and the information generally includes:</p>
                    <ul style="color: #6e727f">
                        <li>First name and Surname</li>
                        <li>Email Address</li>
                        <li>Date of Birth</li>
                        <li>Phone number</li>
                        <li>Address, State, Province, ZIP/Postal code, City</li>
                        <li>Account details</li>
                        <li>BVN</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>By giving us the requested information, you agree to this information being collected and used as described in this privacy policy.</p>

                    <h3 data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="10" style="color: #3C3E82 " class="trim">Other information collected automatically</h3>
                    <ul style="color: #6e727f">
                        <li>Browser or Device Information:  Certain information is collected by most browsers or automatically through your device, such as your computer type (Windows or Macintosh), screen resolution, operating system name and version, device manufacturer and model, language, Internet browser type and version, Media Access Control (MAC) address, and the name and version of the Services (such as the Applications) you are using.  We use this information to ensure that the Services function properly.</li>
                        <li>Application Information:  When you download and use our Applications, we and our service providers may track and collect usage data, such as the date and time the Applications on your device accesses our servers and what information and files have been downloaded to the Applications based on your device number.</li>
                        <li>IP Address:  Your IP address is a number that is automatically assigned to your computer by your Internet Service Provider.  An IP address may be identified and logged automatically in our server log files whenever a user accesses the Services, along with the time of the visit and the page(s) visited.  Collecting IP addresses is standard practice and is done automatically by many websites, applications and other services.  We use IP addresses for purposes such as calculating usage levels, helping diagnose server problems and administering the Services.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3 data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="10" style="color: #3C3E82 " class="trim">How we use the information collected</h3>
                    <p>Reaprite will access and use the data collected to:</p>
                        <ul style="color: #6e727f">
                            <li>Provide you with, or evaluate your eligibility for, products and services that you request from us;</li>
                            <li>Create and Administer your account</li> 
                            <li>Communicate with you about your accounts or transactions with us; and confirm same</li>
                            <li>To update you on available opportunities and promo in the platform.</li>
                            <li>Send regular investment updates and general service information and updates.</li>
                            <li>Send you important information regarding the Services, changes to this Policy and/or other similar administrative information;</li>
                            <li>Send you offers and promotions for our products and services, or products and services that may be of interest to you;</li>
                            <li>Personalize content and experiences in connection with the Services;</li>
                            <li>Verify your identity and/or location (or the identity or location of your authorized representative) for security, fraud prevention and other risk control purposes</li>
                            <li>Optimize or improve our products and services;</li>
                            <li>Detect, investigate and prevent activities that may be illegal or violate our policies;</li>
                            <li>Comply with our legal and regulatory obligations; and</li>
                            <li>Enforce our various terms and conditions and otherwise protect our rights and operations.</li>                      
                        </ul>

                    <h3 data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="10" style="color: #3C3E82 " class="trim">Information sharing</h3>
                        <p>In order to protect your information and keep it private, we do not sell or rent your personal information with third parties. </p>
                        <p>We may only share generic information where necessary, in limited circumstances and not letting out private information, with our business partners and affiliates for Surveys or data projections. Information may also be shared with third party service providers like Google Analytics to monitor and analyse the use of our services.</p>
                        <p>Where also, the Law so requires, or in the interest of any proceedings, the court orders that personal information of a user be disclosed, such may be disclosed in utmost good faith bearing the interest of justice and the privacy of users in mind.</p>
                    
                    <h3 data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-delay="10" style="color: #3C3E82 " class="trim">Information we receives from Third Parties</h3>
